article.headline: Chicago St. 84, N.J. Tech 68
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. -- David Holston scored 18 points and handed out 10 assists to lead Chicago State to an 84-68 win over the New Jersey Institute of Technology on Saturday. John Cantrell and Mike Wilson each added 15 points for the Cougars (15-12), while Carl Montgomery scored 14 points before leaving with an apparent lower back injury after being knocked hard to the floor. Jheryl Wilson had a game-high 26 points for the Highlanders (1-23), while Isaiah Wilkerson added 12 points. The teams traded baskets for most of the first half, with Chicago State holding a 36-32 lead at the break. The Cougars then started the second half with a 13-5 run that featured six points by Montgomery, and they maintained double-digit leads for the rest of the game.
